=Description=

Elias Crim:

"The Chicago-based Kola Nut Collaborative is a mutual support network of people engaged in reciprocal exchange of services, skills, and goods through a timebank where the currency is an hour of time for everyone. It also hosts solidarity economy programs with partners, including Cooperation Chicago. Its director is Michael Tekhen Strode, a Midwestern leader in social innovation and the moderator of this panel."
(https://solidarityhall.org/articles_main/beyond-distributism-to-solidarity-economics/)

